    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-02-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-02-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="111"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d111">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.917 Time/57</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Chief of the Division of Near Eastern
                        Affairs</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Under Secretary of State</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Welles</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-02-18">February 18,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Welles</hi>: I discussed this matter with the Egyptian
                    Minister today, and I think I managed to persuade him that it would be better
                    not to give the incident any further publicity.</p>
                <p>The Minister informed me, incidentally, that a representative of <hi
                        rend="italic">Time</hi> magazine had come to Washington at his request to
                    discuss the whole question, and that he has been assured that the magazine will
                    make “amends” of some kind in a subsequent issue.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wallace Murray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
